===============================
using python 3.6

packages:
numpy
matplotlib

====================================================
1)
mc_perceptron.py
runs multiclass perceptron

if no arguments are given assumes:
- train file resides in ./data/letters.train.data
- test file resides in ./data/letters.test.data

otherwise can be supplied when running script as so:

python mc_perceptron.py <train_file> <test_file>

====================================================
2)
structured_perceptron.py
runs structured perceptron with no added features

if no arguments are given assumes:
- train file resides in ./data/letters.train.data
- test file resides in ./data/letters.test.data

otherwise can be supplied when running script as so:

python structured_perceptron.py <train_file> <test_file>

====================================================
3)
biagram_perceptron.py
runs structured perceptron with no previos letter feature.
outputs test prediction


if no arguments are given assumes:
- train file resides in ./data/letters.train.data
- test file resides in ./data/letters.test.data
- prediction output will be written to ./test.pred

otherwise can be supplied when running script as so:

python structured_perceptron.py <train_file> <test_file> <output_file>

====================================================
4)
heatmap.py

loads w_mat.npy file that was outputed to current directory by biagram_perceptron.py.
outputs w_heatmap.png to current directory.

python heatmap.py


